The paper deals with the problem of sensing wireless microphone signals in the TV white space spectrum, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), cryptography and security (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), and multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed solutions involve statistical decision models and spectral analysis techniques, which are common tools in these sub-categories. Therefore, it is likely that the paper belongs to one or more of these sub-categories.
